WeRateDogs is a popular twitter account created by a college student Matt Nelson in the year 2015 [11].The Twitter account rates people's dogs with a humorous comment about the dog. These ratings almost always have a denominator of 10. However,the numerators are always greater than 10. 11/10, 12/10, 13/10, etc. are some of the typical score. But, Why? Because "they're good dogs Brent." WeRateDogs has over 4 million followers and has received international media coverage. To analyze the data of WeRateDogs data has been gathered from the following three sources:

  1. The WeRateDogs Twitter archive: twitter_archive_enhanced.csv has been received from the Udacity instructor and downloded.

  2. A file (image_predictions.tsv) is hosted on Udacity's servers and has been downloaded programmatically using the Requests library and the specified URL: https://d17h27t6h515a5.cloudfront.net/topher/2017/August/599fd2ad_image-predictions/image-predictions.tsv.

  1. Using the tweet IDs in the WeRateDogs Twitter archive, query have been made of the Twitter API for each tweet's JSON data using Python's Tweepy library and entire set of JSON data has been stored in a file called tweet_json.txt file.

After gathering the data has been cleaned as we have identified 9 quality issues and 02 tidyness issues. After that the following relationship has been explored:

  1. Most frequent dog genres predicted by the algorithm
  1. Most freuqunet dog stages
  1. Time- Year, Month and hour of tweeting
  1. Popular dog names
  1. Correlation coeffiecnt

1. Most frequent dog genres predicted by the algorithm¶

From Figure-1, 2 and 3 following observations can be made.

A. Golden retriever is the most common dog genre predicted by the algorithm in the first instance.

B. Labrador retriever is considered as the second most common category by the algorithm.

C. Most popular categories are common in prediction 1, 2 and 3 with different frequency.
